# ── API-Football (lineups) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Real starting line-ups (formation + per-player grid positions) come from
# API-Football. Copy this file to ".env" and paste your key below — Vite only
# reads ".env" (and .env.local), NOT this .env.example template.
#
# Two ways to access the same data; pick the host that matches your key:
#
#   A) DIRECT — https://dashboard.api-sports.io  (this is what you have)
#      • Sign up, then Dashboard → "My Access" shows your API key.
#      • HOST = v3.football.api-sports.io   (header: x-apisports-key)
#
#   B) RapidAPI marketplace — https://rapidapi.com/api-sports/api/api-football
#      • Subscribe to the Basic (free) plan; the X-RapidAPI-Key value is your key.
#      • HOST = api-football-v1.p.rapidapi.com   (header: X-RapidAPI-Key)
#
# The code auto-detects which header to send from the HOST value below.
#
# NOTE: this is a fully client-side app, so the key ships in the browser bundle.
# Use a free/restricted key here, not a production secret.
VITE_RAPIDAPI_KEY=

# Use the host that matches your key (see A vs B above).
VITE_RAPIDAPI_HOST=v3.football.api-sports.io
